From: CellGov <noreply@cellgov.local>
Subject: [PATCH] cellgov: env-var-gated memory dump at process exit and first RSX put-write

Adds opt-in checkpoint dumps that write configured guest-memory
regions to host files. Up to three triggers per process, all gated
on env vars; no behavior change when none are set.

Triggers and env vars:

  CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH       ProcessExit dump (fires inside
                          _sys_process_exit on the PPU thread).
                          Backward-compatible with prior versions
                          of this patch.

  CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH_RSX   FirstRsxWrite dump (fires inside the RSX
                          thread's cpu_task loop, on the first
                          observed change to the GCM put register
                          from its initial value).

  CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH_RSX2  Second FirstRsxWrite dump (fires on the
                          very next cpu_task iteration after the
                          RSX trigger). Diff against the RSX1 dump
                          bounds the torn-read noise floor.

  CELLGOV_DUMP_REGIONS    Comma-separated `addr:size` hex pairs,
                          shared by all triggers. Each region is
                          appended contiguously in declaration
                          order. See bridges/rpcs3-patch/README.md
                          in the CellGov repo for the manifest
                          contract.

Skews documented in the header and at the trigger:

  1. Poll-observation skew on the RSX trigger: RPCS3's put register
     is plain VM memory with no synchronous store handler, so the
     RSX thread notices put != initial via polling rather than via
     a store hook. The dump fires from the RSX poll loop a few
     microseconds after the guest PPU store.

  2. Torn-read skew on the RSX trigger: the PPU is NOT halted while
     the RSX-thread dump walks 880 KiB of guest memory page-by-page.
     The RSX1-vs-RSX2 diff bounds this empirically; the regions of
     interest (data segment) are expected static at FirstRsxWrite,
     so the bound is expected small.

Read-only with respect to guest state: vm::base() + memcpy to host
file, no scheduler perturbation, no guest memory modification.

Target files: rpcs3/Emu/Cell/lv2/sys_process.cpp,
              rpcs3/Emu/RSX/RSXThread.cpp,
              rpcs3/emucore.vcxproj.

The dump body lives in a new header:
  rpcs3/Emu/Cell/cellgov_checkpoint_dump.h
Copy it from bridges/rpcs3-patch/files/Emu/Cell/ before applying
this patch (mirrors the 0002 workflow).

---

diff --git a/rpcs3/Emu/Cell/lv2/sys_process.cpp b/rpcs3/Emu/Cell/lv2/sys_process.cpp
--- a/rpcs3/Emu/Cell/lv2/sys_process.cpp
+++ b/rpcs3/Emu/Cell/lv2/sys_process.cpp
@@ -342,12 +342,31 @@ error_code sys_process_detach_child(u64 unk)

 extern void signal_system_cache_can_stay();

+// CellGov checkpoint-dump hook. The body lives in
+// Emu/Cell/cellgov_checkpoint_dump.h so the same function can fire
+// from this _sys_process_exit hook and from the RSX-thread cpu_task
+// loop without code duplication. See bridges/rpcs3-patch/README.md
+// in the CellGov repo for the env-var contract.
+#include "Emu/Cell/cellgov_checkpoint_dump.h"
+
 void _sys_process_exit(ppu_thread& ppu, s32 status, u32 arg2, u32 arg3)
 {
 	ppu.state += cpu_flag::wait;

 	sys_process.warning("_sys_process_exit(status=%d, arg2=0x%x, arg3=0x%x)", status, arg2, arg3);

+	// One-shot guard. _sys_process_exit fires once per process under
+	// normal LV2 semantics, so this is belt-and-suspenders; kept for
+	// symmetry with the RSX-thread trigger and to make the hook
+	// re-entry-safe under any future LV2 path that loops back here.
+	{
+		static std::atomic_flag cellgov_process_exit_fired{};
+		if (!cellgov_process_exit_fired.test_and_set())
+		{
+			cellgov::cellgov_checkpoint_dump("CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH");
+		}
+	}
+
 	Emu.CallFromMainThread([]()
 	{
 		sys_process.success("Process finished");
diff --git a/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/RSXThread.cpp b/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/RSXThread.cpp
--- a/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/RSXThread.cpp
+++ b/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/RSXThread.cpp
@@ -1,6 +1,9 @@
 #include "stdafx.h"
 #include "RSXThread.h"

+// CellGov FirstRsxWrite dump hook. See bridges/rpcs3-patch/README.md.
+#include "Emu/Cell/cellgov_checkpoint_dump.h"
+
 #include "Capture/rsx_capture.h"
 #include "Common/surface_store.h"
 #include "Core/RSXReservationLock.hpp"
@@ -1122,6 +1125,44 @@ namespace rsx

 		while (!test_stopped())
 		{
+			// CellGov FirstRsxWrite checkpoint dump. Fires up to twice
+			// per process: once when ctrl->put first differs from its
+			// initial value (the guest's first put-register write),
+			// and again on the very next cpu_task iteration. The diff
+			// between the two output files bounds the torn-read noise
+			// floor from sampling 880 KiB of guest memory while the
+			// PPU keeps executing. See README in
+			// bridges/rpcs3-patch/ for the env-var contract and the
+			// two skews documented at the trigger.
+			{
+				static std::atomic_flag cellgov_rsx1_fired{};
+				static std::atomic_flag cellgov_rsx2_fired{};
+				static u32 cellgov_initial_put = 0xFFFFFFFFu;
+				if (ctrl && !cellgov_rsx2_fired.test(std::memory_order_relaxed))
+				{
+					const u32 cur_put = static_cast<u32>(ctrl->put.load());
+					if (cellgov_initial_put == 0xFFFFFFFFu)
+					{
+						cellgov_initial_put = cur_put;
+					}
+					else if (cur_put != cellgov_initial_put)
+					{
+						const u32 cur_get = static_cast<u32>(ctrl->get.load());
+						if (!cellgov_rsx1_fired.test_and_set())
+						{
+							std::fprintf(stderr, "[cellgov] RSX1 trigger: put=0x%x initial=0x%x get=0x%x\n",
+								cur_put, cellgov_initial_put, cur_get);
+							cellgov::cellgov_checkpoint_dump("CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH_RSX");
+						}
+						else if (!cellgov_rsx2_fired.test_and_set())
+						{
+							std::fprintf(stderr, "[cellgov] RSX2 trigger: put=0x%x initial=0x%x get=0x%x\n",
+								cur_put, cellgov_initial_put, cur_get);
+							cellgov::cellgov_checkpoint_dump("CELLGOV_DUMP_PATH_RSX2");
+						}
+					}
+				}
+			}
+
 			// Wait for external pause events
 			if (external_interrupt_lock)
 			{
diff --git a/rpcs3/emucore.vcxproj b/rpcs3/emucore.vcxproj
--- a/rpcs3/emucore.vcxproj
+++ b/rpcs3/emucore.vcxproj
@@ -971,6 +971,7 @@
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUCallback.h" />
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUDisAsm.h" />
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUFunction.h" />
+    <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\cellgov_checkpoint_dump.h" />
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUInterpreter.h" />
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUOpcodes.h" />
     <ClInclude Include="Emu\Cell\PPUThread.h" />
